{
  "children": [
    {
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "value": "Cognitive Load Theory"
        }
      ],
      "id": "cognitive-load",
      "level": 1,
      "type": "heading"
    },
    {
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "value": "Cognitive load theory, developed by John Sweller"
        },
        {
          "label": "sweller1988",
          "type": "footnote_ref"
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "value": ", describes the mental effort required to process information."
        }
      ],
      "type": "paragraph"
    },
    {
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "value": "Types of Cognitive Load"
        }
      ],
      "level": 2,
      "type": "heading"
    },
    {
      "items": [
        {
          "definitions": [
            [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "value": "The inherent difficulty of the material itself"
              }
            ]
          ],
          "term": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "value": "Intrinsic load"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "definitions": [
            [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "value": "Load caused by poor instructional design"
              }
            ]
          ],
          "term": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "value": "Extraneous load"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "definitions": [
            [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "value": "Load devoted to building mental schemas"
              }
            ]
          ],
          "term": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "value": "Germane load"
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "type": "definition_list"
    },
    {
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "value": "Connection to Software Design"
        }
      ],
      "level": 2,
      "type": "heading"
    },
    {
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "value": "Software complexity is directly related to cognitive load"
        },
        {
          "label": "complexity",
          "type": "footnote_ref"
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "value": ". Clean code practices reduce "
        },
        {
          "children": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "value": "extraneous load"
            }
          ],
          "type": "bold"
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "value": " by making code easier to parse visually."
        }
      ],
      "type": "paragraph"
    },
    {
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "value": "See "
        },
        {
          "target": "Clean Code Principles",
          "type": "wiki_link"
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "value": " and "
        },
        {
          "target": "Software Complexity Metrics",
          "type": "wiki_link"
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "value": "."
        }
      ],
      "type": "paragraph"
    },
    {
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "value": "This connects to the idea of "
        },
        {
          "children": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "value": "chunking"
            }
          ],
          "type": "highlight"
        },
        {
          "label": "miller1956",
          "type": "footnote_ref"
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "value": " -- grouping information into meaningful units reduces working memory demands."
        }
      ],
      "type": "paragraph"
    },
    {
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "value": "Implications for API Design"
        }
      ],
      "level": 2,
      "type": "heading"
    },
    {
      "children": [
        {
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "value": "Good API design minimizes the cognitive load on the consumer. Every unnecessary option, parameter, or configuration point adds to the burden."
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        }
      ],
      "type": "blockquote"
    },
    {
      "children": [
        {
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "value": "This principle applies equally to CLI tools and library interfaces."
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        }
      ],
      "foldable": false,
      "kind": "note",
      "type": "admonition"
    },
    {
      "children": [
        {
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "value": "Sweller, J. (1988). Cognitive load during problem solving."
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        }
      ],
      "label": "sweller1988",
      "type": "footnote_def"
    },
    {
      "children": [
        {
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "value": "See the discussion in "
            },
            {
              "target": "Accidental vs Essential Complexity",
              "type": "wiki_link"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "value": "."
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        }
      ],
      "label": "complexity",
      "type": "footnote_def"
    },
    {
      "children": [
        {
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "value": "Miller, G.A. (1956). The magical number seven, plus or minus two."
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        }
      ],
      "label": "miller1956",
      "type": "footnote_def"
    }
  ]
}